  "text": "The selection of the system boundary should be consistent with the goal of the study, and the criteria used to establish the system boundary should be identified and explained (ISO 14044 2006) . In aquaculture systems, the length of the full production chain is largely dependent on the type of system (Fig. 1) . For example, external inputs of feed and hatchery-reared juveniles may not be needed in extensive systems and if the product is sold fresh on the market it needs no processing (e.g., carp in China). Fish and seafood are also the most perishable of food products, and the level of processing will influence the longevity of the product, as well as the amounts wasted, hence the environmental impacts [CITATION_1] .",
